OL,7,FThe issue of baptism has come to the
OL,8,Fpolitical forefront after the case of
OL,9,Falkali attack suspect Abdul Ezedi, who
OL,10,Fsuccessfully challenged his asylum
OL,11,Frefusal after converting to
OL,12,FChristianity.
OL,14,FEzedi, who lived in Newcastle, is
OL,15,Fbelieved to have been supported in his
OL,16,Fclaim by someone from a Baptist
OL,17,Fchurch, rather than the Church of
OL,18,FEngland, but the case has prompted
OL,19,Fdebate on the issue of conversions.
