OL,7,FAsked who brought the asylum seekers
OL,8,Fto him, Mr Firth said: "There was a
OL,9,Fparticular individual who I think had
OL,10,Freceived right to remain in the UK
OL,11,Fthrough the asylum application system.
OL,13,F"But I think this particular
OL,14,Findividual didn't want baptism but was
OL,15,Fbringing lots of people who this
OL,16,Findividual said need to be baptised."
OL,18,FIt was put to him that only 15 people
OL,19,Fwho may have been asylum seekers were
OL,20,Fbaptised at St Cuthbert's over 10
OL,21,Fyears.
