OL,7,F"They were not really wanting to get
OL,8,Finvolved in the life of the church so
OL,9,Fmuch after I requested them to do so."
OL,11,FIn response Mr Firth's claims, a
OL,12,Fspokesperson for the Diocese of Durham
OL,13,Fsaid: "As the Bishop of Chelmsford
OL,14,Fsaid to today's Select Committee, we
OL,15,Fhave not seen any evidence to support
OL,16,Fthe claim made by Matthew Firth that
OL,17,Fthe Church of England is being used as
OL,18,Fa 'conveyer belt' for baptisms in
OL,19,Forder for people to gain asylum status.
